      "description": "Available is a mechanically robust E92 M3, powered by the S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This high-performance mill features individual throttle bodies and a 12.0:1 compression ratio, delivering a linear power curve all the way to its 8,400 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise 6-speed manual gearbox and the M Variable Differential Lock, ensuring optimal torque distribution across the rear axle. The chassis retains its structural integrity, featuring Electronic Damper Control (EDC) and aluminum multi-link suspension geometry for exceptional lateral grip. Preventive maintenance has been prioritized, including the critical rod bearing service and throttle actuator replacement. This example features the weight-saving carbon fiber roof and remains a visceral, analog driving machine for the serious enthusiast.",
